Abstract: In the paper we consider a new class (called NoLoess) of nonparametric estimators of regression function r(x) = E(Y jX = x): The new estimators link nonparametric and parametric methods. NoLoess extends the class of Macauley, Cleveland, and Stone estimators and replaces their locally linear models (Loess) given by (1.3) with a general locally parametric nonlinear model g(x; ). The parameter is estimated locally by fitting g(x; ) to a sub-sample (X i 1 ; Y i 1 ); : : : ; (X i k (x) ; Y i k (x) ) with X i 1 ; : : : ; X i k (x) being close to x. The resulting nonparametric estimator of r(x) is of the form g(x; ^ )(x). Under proper regularity assumptions it is strongly consistent. 
